{"id":833,"category_slug":"ielts-listening","category_name":"IELTS Listening","position":197,"title":"Cam8 - Test 2 - Part 1","subtitle":"Insurance Claim Phone Call","level":"B1","parts":90,"url":"https://dailydictation.com/exercises/ielts-listening/cam8-test-2-part-1.833/listen-and-type","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-8-test-2-part-1-2023-07-25-20-15-20/0-ielts-cambridge-8-test-2-part-1.mp3","transcript":"Good morning. Total Insurance.\nJudy speaking, how may I help you?\nI recently shipped my belongings from overseas back here to Australia\nand I took out insurance with your company.\nSome items were damaged during the move so I need to make a claim.\nWhat do I have to do?\nOkay, well first I need to get a few details about this.\nCan you give me your name please?\nYes. It's Michael Alexander.\nOkay. And your address, please?\nMy old address or my current one?\nYour current one.\nIt's 24 Manly Street, Milperra near Sydney.\nWhat was the suburb, sorry?\nMilperra.\nMILPERRA.\nRight.\nNow, who was the shipping agent, Mr Alexander?\nYou mean the company we used?\nYes, the company who packed everything up at the point of origin.\nOh, it was... erm...\nFirst Class Movers.\nOkay...\nwhere were the goods shipped from?\nChina,\nbut the ship came via Singapore and was there for about a week.\nDon't worry, all of that information will be in the documentation.\nNow, the dates.\nDo you know when the ship arrived?\nIt left on the 11th of October\nand got to Sydney on the 28th of November.\nOkay.\nI need one more thing.\nThere's a reference number.\nIt should be in the top right-hand corner of the pink form they gave you.\nUh... let me have a look.\nUh, yes, here it is.\nIt's 601ACK.\nThanks.\nI need to take down a few details of the actual damage over the phone before you put in a full report.\nCan you tell me how many items were damaged and what the damage was?\nYes, well four things actually.\nI'll start with the big things.\nMy TV first of all.\nIt's a large one... very expensive.\nOur insurance doesn't cover electrical problems.\nIt isn't an electrical problem.\nThe screen has a huge crack in it so it's unusable.\nI see.\nAny idea of the price to repair it?\nNo.\nWell, I don't think it can be repaired.\nIt will need a new one.\nOkay.\nI'll make a note of that and we'll see what we can do.\nNow, what was the second item?\nThe cabinet from the bathroom was damaged as well.\nIt's a lovely cabinet, we use it to keep our towels in.\nAnd what is the extent of the damage?\nWell, the back and the sides seem okay\nbut the door has a huge hole in it.\nIt can't be repaired.\nI'm really not very happy about it.\nAnd how much do you think it will cost to replace it?\nWell, when I bought it last year, I paid $125 for it.\nBut the one I've seen here in Sydney is a bit more expensive,\nit's $140.\nRight, and what was the third item?\nMy dining room table.\nIt's a lovely table from Indonesia.\nIt must have been very hot inside the container\nbecause one leg has completely split down the middle.\nThe top and the other three look okay, thank goodness.\nAny idea of the price to repair it?\nWell, I had an estimate done on this actually because it is a very special table to us.\nThey quoted us $200, which is really pricey\nso I hope the insurance will cover the total cost.\nI'm sure that will be fine.\nWhat was the last item, Mr Alexander?\nWell, we have a lovely set of china plates and dishes,\nyou know, with matching cups, saucers, the lot.\nThey were all in the one box which must have got dropped because some plates were broken - six actually.\nAnd can you tell me the replacement value of these?\nWell, it's hard to say because they were part of a set\nbut they can be up to $10 each as it's such a good set.\nOkay, so that would be around $60 altogether?\nYes, that's right.\nAnd is that all of the items?\nYes.\nSo what do I have to do now?","youtube_video_id":"","details_cached_at":"2026-06-15T20:51:06","challenges":[{"position":1,"content":"Good morning. Total Insurance.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-8-test-2-part-1-2023-07-25-20-15-20/1.mp3","time_start":0.39,"time_end":2.28},{"position":2,"content":"Judy speaking, how may I help you?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-8-test-2-part-1-2023-07-25-20-15-20/2.mp3","time_start":2.28,"time_end":4.07},{"position":3,"content":"I recently shipped my belongings from overseas back here to Australia","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-8-test-2-part-1-2023-07-25-20-15-20/3.mp3","time_start":4.19,"time_end":8.41},{"position":4,"content":"and I took out insurance with your company.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-8-test-2-part-1-2023-07-25-20-15-20/4.mp3","time_start":8.41,"time_end":11.36},{"position":5,"content":"Some items were damaged during the move so I need to make a claim.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-8-test-2-part-1-2023-07-25-20-15-20/5.mp3","time_start":11.36,"time_end":15.64},{"position":6,"content":"What do I have to do?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-8-test-2-part-1-2023-07-25-20-15-20/6.mp3","time_start":15.64,"time_end":16.79},{"position":7,"content":"Okay, well first I need to get a few details about this.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-8-test-2-part-1-2023-07-25-20-15-20/7.mp3","time_start":16.79,"time_end":20.76},{"position":8,"content":"Can you give me your name please?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-8-test-2-part-1-2023-07-25-20-15-20/8.mp3","time_start":20.76,"time_end":22.87},{"position":9,"content":"Yes. It's Michael Alexander.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-8-test-2-part-1-2023-07-25-20-15-20/9.mp3","time_start":22.87,"time_end":25.77},{"position":10,"content":"Okay. And your address, please?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-8-test-2-part-1-2023-07-25-20-15-20/10.mp3","time_start":25.77,"time_end":28.49},{"position":11,"content":"My old address or my current one?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-8-test-2-part-1-2023-07-25-20-15-20/11.mp3","time_start":28.49,"time_end":30.97},{"position":12,"content":"Your current one.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-8-test-2-part-1-2023-07-25-20-15-20/12.mp3","time_start":30.97,"time_end":32.07},{"position":13,"content":"It's 24 Manly Street, Milperra near Sydney.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-8-test-2-part-1-2023-07-25-20-15-20/13.mp3","time_start":32.07,"time_end":37.05},{"position":14,"content":"What was the suburb, sorry?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-8-test-2-part-1-2023-07-25-20-15-20/14.mp3","time_start":37.29,"time_end":38.93},{"position":15,"content":"Milperra.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-8-test-2-part-1-2023-07-25-20-15-20/15.mp3","time_start":38.93,"time_end":39.95},{"position":16,"content":"MILPERRA.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-8-test-2-part-1-2023-07-25-20-15-20/16.mp3","time_start":39.95,"time_end":44.79},{"position":17,"content":"Right.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-8-test-2-part-1-2023-07-25-20-15-20/17.mp3","time_start":44.79,"time_end":45.61},{"position":18,"content":"Now, who was the shipping agent, Mr Alexander?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-8-test-2-part-1-2023-07-25-20-15-20/18.mp3","time_start":45.61,"time_end":48.96},{"position":19,"content":"You 